Application invited for a special scholarship-supported master program 2021 at the
Faculty of science and technology, UiT The Arctic University of Norway
This document contains the information about submitting an application for a special scholarship-
supported master program 2021 at the Faculty of science and technology, UiT The Arctic University of
Norway. In 2020, UiT had signed MoUs with the following Indian institutes of education:
 Indian Institute of Technology, new Delhi, India
 Indian Institute of Technology (Indian School of Mines), Dhanbad, India
 Indian Institute of Technology, Guwahati, India
 Indraprastha Institute of Information technology, New Delhi, India
As a follow up, and in order to support the joint research and education interests, UiT has organised a
pilot master program for bachelor students who are either graduating in 2021 or have already graduated
from the above institutions. Students from other institutions are not eligible for this special program, and
may apply through the normal annual master program intake of UiT.
There are a maximum of five positions in this special program, and the students selected will be provided
with monthly student scholarships for the 2-year period of the master program. Therefore, no declaration
of financial ability is involved.

Document list for making an application:
Your application must include: A cover letter (self written by the candidate), a curriculum vitae,
transcripts and degree certificate (if graduated), English proficiency certificate/score sheet, valid id
document (passport front page that contains photograph)
Your application may include: Publication list, articles/pre-prints in which the applicant is an author,
bachelor project report/plan (if your degree includes a final year project component), Non-academic
publication/scientific presence list (such as source code sites(github, etc.), other coursework(such as
coursera, etc.), participation in challenges, olympiads, other academic/co-curricular achievements etc.),
proof of name change (if applicable), other documents which may help in competitive positioning of the
candidate.
Remark: A formal check-list of required documents is included here
https://en.uit.no/education/admissions/art?p_document_id=594510 . Note that no declaration or
documentation of financial ability is needed for this program.

The cover letter:
The cover letter should address the following questions at least, while the candidate is free to include
more information.
 What topics are of interest to you, have you recognized a group/person you would like to work
with.
 Which program(s)/study area(s) do you want to apply for
 What is your motivation to apply for masters, why UiT/Tromsø/Norway
 What are your career aspirations
 Why do you think you are a good candidate

Selection process:
Due to the limited number of positions and scholarship support, the selection is competitive and is based
on a combination of several factors. Based on the submitted application, an initial shortlist will be
performed to identify the candidates for the next stage and contacted.
Candidates shortlisted will appear for interviews. For master in computer science* applications, a code
task must be submitted with the application package
(https://en.uit.no/Content/596000/Programming_task.pdf) , other master applicants may also be given
some test tasks after the shortlisting.
Candidates will be selected based on CV, cover letter, overall performance in interview and test task(s),
personal suitability of the candidate, and other factors.
